1- What is a server:
	is a computer that serve 

2- What is the role of the domain name:
	human readable name to access a web site

3- What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com:
	CNAME

4- What is the role of the web server:
	provide (web page, video, images, etc.) static files

5- What is the role of the application server:
	allow you to interacte with web site

6- What is the role of the database:
	store the data for future uses

7- What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website:
	either HTTP/HTTPS

Issues with this infrastructure:

*- SPOF:
	becuase you have one server if any thing happen to it you lose everythinh

*- Downtime:
	also becuase its one server that mean if you try to update users can't access and they have to wait
*- scalling:
	can not handle scalling because of the limitted resourcse and here is we have just one server
